## Code files

| File | What it does |
|---|---|
| **load.py** | Loads everything once, holds it in memory, runs the pipeline + matching when a query comes in. Start once, leave open. |
| **test_manual.py** | Sends your query to load.py and prints results. Re-run per query. |
| **config.py** | Settings (project ID, API URL, model) + pickle paths. |
| **artifacts.py** | Loads the heavy pickles (network graph, IC, topics) once. |
| **document.py** | Reads the synthetic document chunks from `reconstructed_obj.pk`. |
| **intents.py** | LLM query breakdown -> intents, sub-natures, atomic concepts. |
| **cui_core.py** | Calls the extraction API to turn text into CUIs. |
| **cui_summarizer.py** | Reduces a big CUI list to the important surviving CUIs. |
| **topic_adaptor.py** | Looks up topics for CUIs; matches query vs doc (top-3-by-IC scoring). |
| **build_topics.py** | Builds `topics.pkl`. Run once; NOT used during the demo. |
| **diagnose_topics.py** | Checks topic quality (anchor specificity, purity, overlap). |

---

## Data files (required)

| File | What it holds |
|---|---|
| **topics.pkl** | Prebuilt topic buckets. |
| **isa_precomputed.pkl** | Precomputed IS-A ancestors + IC from the network graph. |
| **networkx_cui_context_v1_3_0.pkl** | The network graph (~1.6 GB). |
| **ic_precomputed.pkl** | IC scores used by the summarizer. |
| **reconstructed_obj.pk** | The synthetic documents and their text chunks. |

