## Handy lookups

**What CUIs are in a topic:**
```python
import pickle
P = pickle.load(open("topics.pkl", "rb"))
TOPIC_ID = "tp_xxxxxxxxxxxx"
t = P["topic_id_to_topic"].get(TOPIC_ID)
print(f"anchor {t['canonical']} | size {t['size']} | IC {t['anchor_ic']:.3f}")
for cui in sorted(t["members"]):
    print(" ", cui, P["labels"].get(cui, cui))
```

**Total number of topics:**
```python
print(len(P["topic_id_to_topic"]), "topics")
```

