## Known limitations

- **Laterality** (left vs right knee) is NOT separated. The SNOMED IS-A
  hierarchy treats left/right knee as identical (laterality is a separate
  axis not in the graph), so they group into the same topic. The top-3-by-IC
  scoring reduces this leak, but full separation would need laterality data
  from MRREL (not currently loaded).
- A few **broad topics** (low IC, large size) exist. They are harmless — the
  top-3-by-IC scoring keeps them out of matches.
